content:
Automate and Migrate User Access with User Access Policies (Generally Available)

Automate your usersâ€™ assignments to permission sets, package licenses, public groups, and other access features based on criteria that you set. Create policies that automatically grant or remove access whenever users are created or updated. Or, easily migrate large sets of users to a new access setup in a single operation.

You can now create 200 active policies, up from 20, and set the order in which active policies are run. This feature was delivered thanks to your ideas on IdeaExchange.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) in Enterprise and Unlimited editions.

How: From Setup, turn on User Access Policies, then create or manage user access policies.

title: Automating User Access with Salesforce
